F. Solution Strategy
The proposed multi-objective problem formulation, with
objective in (15), for the optimal placement and sizing of
fast EV charging stations in a coupled transportation network
and EPDN is solved by Particle Swarm Optimization with
Constriction Factor (PSO-CF).1 As mentioned in [33] and [34],
the use of a constriction factor improves the search ability
and ensures convergence stability of PSO. The algorithm
uses a population of particles, which possess a position and
velocity. The best position of a particle in search space is
found to optimize the objective’s value. The standard equations
to update the velocity and position of particles in PSO-CF
are [33] and [34]
