III. NUMERIC RESULTS AND DISCUSSION
A 30-node, 33 kV primary EPDN coupled with a 25-node
transportation network [13] is used to evaluate the performance
of the proposed formulation. The EPDN’s bus connectivity
is based on the IEEE 30-bus system [37]. The single line
diagrams of EPDN and the transportation network are given
in Fig. 3 and Fig. 4, respectively. The distance, in kilometres
between the nodes in each network, is represented on the lines
connecting the nodes. The electrical line parameters of EPDN
are given in Table II. In the EPDN, Bus 1 is considered as the
reference bus. The coupling is accomplished by mapping the
transportation nodes to the EPDN nodes using the distances
between the lines connecting the nodes, as shown in Table III.
The analysis is done for a five-year planning period, with
the growth rate of non-EV load assumed to be 3% per year.
To evaluate the performance of the proposed formulation,
a critical scenario is considered, in which the peak of the
non-EV load coincides with the peak of the EV charging
load during rush hour. Therefore, the analysis is carried out
for the cumulative peak load. The heterogeneous mobility
