C. Base Case Analysis With Different Methods
The proposed formulation is analysed for the base case with
the PSO, PSO-CF, and MPSPSO. The base case is considers
the condition of 4% growth rate of EVs per year, i.e., 2000
EVs enter the transportation network with initial SOC range
(SOCo) of 0.45-0.6. Values of all the objectives along with
the computation time per trial are evaluated with each method
and a comparison is done.
It is observed from Table VI
that both the PSO variants, i.e., the PSO-CF and MPSPSO
have performed better than the traditional PSO. However, the
maximum traffic coverage is obtained with the PSO-CF. Even
with the traffic coverage upto 95%, PSO-CF achieves least
values for the power loss, queuing time, VDI, total cost, and
the computation time in comparison to the MPSPSO and PSO.
Since, the performance of PSO-CF is observed to be better
than the MPSPSO and PSO, therefore, further analysis is
carried out using PSO-CF. The computation time obtained for
50 trials with PSO-CF is 52.72 hours.
