B. Electric Vehicle Charging Station Modeling: 
Electric car batteries are charged at stations known as 
electric vehicle charging stations (EVCS) [14]. Typically, 
the energy rating of EV batteries is indicated in kWh and 
Ah. Therefore, the main presumption for modeling the 
EVCS is that it only provides the EV battery with the 
necessary real current. Any bus's actual power is enhanced 
if EVCS is linked to it. As a result, these EVCS are 
strategically placed in regions where branch currents are at 
their lowest. Assume that bus d from Fig. 2 is the best bus 
for EVCS placement. The active power in addition to the 
power required for already existed load is drawn by EVCS 
from this bus d. 
 
