III. OPTIMIZATION TOOL 
Min-Yuan Cheng and Doddy Prayogo proposed the SOS 
algorithm in 2014 [11]. SOS is a powerful and robust 
metaheuristic algorithm which has been implemented to solve 
optimization and complex engineering design issues. This 
algorithm mimics the symbiotic interaction techniques that 
organisms adapt for survival in the nature. The SOS algorithm 
resembles the real-world biological relationship in three 
phases i.e., mutualism, commensalism, and parasitism. 
Mutualism refers to the symbiotic interaction among two 
different species in which both the organisms is benefitted. 
Commensalism refers to the symbiotic interaction among two 
different organisms where one benefits while the other one is 
unharmed. Parasitism refers to the symbiotic interaction 
among two different organisms where one is benefitted while 
the other one is actively affected [12]. The SOS algorithm has 
been implemented in this research paper for searching the 
optimal nodes for the allocation of EVCS. 
For optimal allocation of EVCS, the proposed flow chart 
is being presented in fig. 1. In this research paper, the search 
agent denotes the location of random nodes where EVCS will 
be connected. For calculating the objective function, we have 
used the distribution system’s backward forward sweep load 
flow technique along with various constraints. The locations 
of EVCS will be updated according to the SOS optimization 
method.  
