V. CONCLUSIONS 
    The inadequate number of EVCS is the most significant 
barrier in acceptance of EV on large scale. This paper 
proposes a realistic solution on optimal placement of EVCS 
considering the charging stations are widely distributed for 
maximum accessibility as it is a consumer-oriented service. 
The SOS algorithm has been applied to solve the allocation 
issues and the obtained results shows that the solution is 
optimal and robust. It has been noticed that the placement of 
EVCS has a significant impact on the distribution network. 
Real power loss and level of voltage drop minimization 
should not be the only objective but providing EVCS access 
to widespread area is much more feasible and realistic. 
