formulated by Deb et al. [1] that takes into account distribu-
tion network operating parameters such as voltage stability,
reliability, and power loss together under a single frame. One
more salient feature of the VRP index is that it takes into
account both frequency and duration based reliability indices.
The suitable value, such as minimum or maximum of the
VRP index cannot be generalized and is dependent on the
test network. A low value of VRP index is desirable. Ideally,
the minimum value of VRP index is 1 when there is no
increase in the load. VRP index is mathematically expressed
