D. EFFECT OF CHARGING STATION PLACEMENT
ON DISTRIBUTION NETWORK
The charging stations affect the operating parameters of the
distribution network such as voltage deviation, reliability, and
power loss. However, the voltage proﬁles of all the buses
(Fig. 7) were within acceptable limit for all the six plans
reported in Table 8. Fig. 8, Fig. 9 and Fig. 10 show the
impact of charging station placement on the three reliabil-
ity indices named SAIFI, SAIDI, and CAIDI respectively.
