The Silhouette Coefﬁcient is deﬁned for each EV x and is composed of two scores: the
average distance between an EV and all other EVs in the same cluster, i.e., a(x), and the
average distance between an EV and all other EVs in the next nearest cluster, i.e., b(x). The
Silhouette Coefﬁcient for a set of EVs is given as the mean of the Silhouette Coefﬁcient for
